- `EffectiveConcurrencyConfig` carries all fields needed to drive `checkConcurrencyLimits` ✓
- `getEffectiveConfig(config, now?)` — default `now = new Date()` allows deterministic overrides in tests ✓

`scripts/ops/concurrency-simulation.test.ts`:
- Imports `getEffectiveConfig` (named export) and `ConcurrencyConfig` (type import) from `./concurrency-config.js` ✓
- Existing `POLICY` constant does not include `trial` — satisfies `ConcurrencyConfig` because `trial` is optional ✓
- All 8 new test cases are logically correct (see invariant checks below)

### New test case invariant checks

| Test | Expected outcome | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `TRIAL_DISABLED` → base limits | `total=6, claude=2, codex=4, trial_active=false` | `enabled: false` → base path |
| `TRIAL_ACTIVE` future expiry → trial limits | `total=8, claude=3, codex=5, trial_active=true` | `enabled=true`, `allowed_until` > now |
| `TRIAL_EXPIRED` → base limits | `total=6, trial_active=false` | `allowed_until` < now → auto-revert |
| `allowed_until: null` → never expires | `total=8, trial_active=true, trial_expires_at=null` | null means no expiry |
| 7th lane under trial (6 active) | 0 violations | total(8) > active(6), codex(3) < limit(5) |
| 9th lane under trial (8 active) | ≥1 violation | active(8) ≥ total(8) → total_cap_exceeded |
| 7th lane after expiry (6 active) | ≥1 violation | base total(6), active(6) → total_cap_exceeded + claude_cap_exceeded |
| unsafe lane above base cap | `trial_unsafe_lane_type` | slots above base 6 are restricted to `safe_types_only` |

